dataObjects.title: Biology
dataObjects.description: Occurs in the middle and upper water layers.  Feeds on worms, small crustaceans and insects (Ref. 7020).  Aquarium keeping:  in groups of 5 or more individuals; minimum aquarium size 60 cm (Ref. 51150).

dataObjects.subject: http://rs.tdwg.org/ontology/voc/SPMInfoItems#Distribution
dataObjects.description: South America:  Paraguay and Guaporé River basins to Argentina (Ref. 9086).

dataObjects.subject: http://rs.tdwg.org/ontology/voc/SPMInfoItems#Size
dataObjects.title: Max. size
dataObjects.description: 7.5 cm SL (male/unsexed; (Ref. 81048))
